beer_name: Moylans Hopsickle Imperial India Pale Ale

review_blob: The lemons are very prominent. Not sure lemon is a good flavor match for a hoppy IPA. Still, Im going to finish this bottle.
beer_name: Dogfish Head Hellhound On My Ale

review_blob: Good. Mild aroma. Virtually no head. Deep amber color. Quite bitter but with a touch of sweetness. Seems to be widely available.

It's hard to believe that this brew contains only 6% alcohol. It tastes much stronger than that. Wonderful grapefruit on the palate. Expensive, but an excellent beer to be sure.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

The term "wet hop" apparently refers to the use of hops when they are fresh off the vine, prior to being dried. For that reason, wet hopped beers are only available in the fall. This one seems to be the best one. It's very good.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Really delicious. I'm not talented at describing taste, but again I say it is delicious.

This must be one of my favorites. Like racer five, but stronger and hoppier. Very nice.

Reminiscent of Heady Topper. Honey, flowers, hops. Really pleasant aroma. And that is about how all I have to say about it.
